80.7	Michael_Milken	Michael Milken	Michael Robert Milken (born July 4, 1946) is an American business magnate, financier, and philanthropist noted for his role in the development of the market for high-yield bonds (also called junk bonds) during the 1970s and 1980s, for his 1990 guilty plea to felony charges for violating US securities laws, and for his funding of medical research.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/76/Michael_Milken_1.jpg/220px-Michael_Milken_1.jpg
